comment_data.body:
Given that this can return 6 values, shouldn't we have:
```suggestion
    Return (multiple): ~
        (`integer`)
        (`integer`)
        (`integer`)
        (`integer`)
        (`integer|nil`)
        (`integer|nil`)
```
For my own learning: Why do we need to use the deprecated function here?

comment_data.body: There's an overload that covers that. LuaLS is really bad at handling this function so I'd rather just get it to work for now. We can amend this when LuaLS gets better.
We don't have to, but whoever deprecated it didn't update the internal uses. It's not going to be removed until 1.0 so it's low risk anyway.

comment_data.body:
Fair enough.

Also, if I understand https://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/master/scripts/cdoc_grammar.lua correctly, we don't handle `@overload` in our docs generation right?
I think we should then remove the definitions using `@alias` in the meta file and keep these as they are. The enum would provide better completion support.
